{'text': "Wouldn't it be better to legalize drugs for medicinal purposes instead of completely legalizing them? Why do we need to criminalize every aspect of the life of a human being?"}
{'text': "I don't like the idea of people doing drugs because I feel like it's wrong."}
{'text': 'If we legalize drugs, how many people will try them? How many people will get sick from them?'}
{'text': "Just imagine the way the world would be if we had legalized sex before we legalized drugs. We wouldn't have to worry about STDs."}

{'text': "(4) If the government legalized marijuana, they could still arrest people for using pot, but they could no longer arrest people for using cocaine, heroin, methamphetamine, or anything else that's illegal."}
{'text': '(8) If you legalize drugs, then you might actually reduce the amount of people who go to prison for drug offenses, and thus reduce the amount of people who go to prison for other crimes.'}
{'text': "Don't you think that if we legalize drugs, there will be more people using drugs?"}

{'text': "Why don't they just decriminalize the possession of all illegal drugs, keep the selling of illegal drugs up to the states, and leave the cultivation of marijuana up to the individual states?"}
{'text': '(9) If you legalize drugs, you might actually end up having less people get busted for drugs than if they were still illegal.'}
{'text': 'It has been proven time and time again that laws against drugs are ineffective, and do nothing to help the people who need them the most.'}
{'text': "If you're against the legalization of drugs, then you must be against all drugs."}
{'text': "(8) Legalizing drugs would decrease the violence associated with the drug trade. It's true that drug trafficking is a violent business, but at least it uses violence to make money."}
{'text': 'What if we were to actually provide drug treatment services to addicts instead of arresting them for using them? That would be much more effective, and much less expensive.'}
{'text': 'It is easy to imagine a world where everyone was allowed to smoke cigarettes. The problem would be the prevalence of addiction.'}
{'text': "I don't think that it's ever good for society to have large numbers of addicts."}

{'text': 'What if we were to legalize drugs, but instead focus on providing drug treatment services to addicts rather than arresting them for using them? That would still be much more effective, and less expensive.'}
{'text': "I don't think it's ever good for society to have large numbers of addicts."}

{'text': '(9) The prohibition of drugs causes harm to society in several ways. By creating a market for drugs, the government punishes people who use drugs and tries to take away their rights as citizens.'}
{'text': 'We have no reason to legalize drugs because drugs are not dangerous. \xa0In fact, there is quite a lot of evidence that drugs are actually safer than alcohol.'}

{'text': 'You know what would be even more effective than legalization of drugs? \xa0If we were really serious about providing drug treatment services to addicts, rather than arresting them for using drugs.'}
{'text': 'Why not legalize prostitution and sex work?'}
{'text': "Imagine that you're a libertarian and you live in America."}
{'text': 'Would it cause more people to use drugs than if they were legal? I think not.'}
{'text': 'If drugs are legalized, they will be regulated. \xa0There will be a strict set of standards for testing the purity of the drugs.'}
{'text': "As long as we legalize heroin, meth, and cocaine, then we can't possibly replace them with something worse."}
{'text': 'A society that cannot distinguish between a person who has a legitimate medical need for a drug, and a person who is using that drug for non-medical reasons, is not a free society.'}
{'text': "(3) Most drugs are highly addictive, and it's impossible to stop using them. Once you start, you can never stop."}
{'text': 'You can legalize drugs and still criminalize the possession, manufacture, and distribution of marijuana, heroin, crack, cocaine, meth, etc.'}
{'text': 'The average drug dealer is probably not a particularly good guy. He probably has problems in his own life. Maybe he was abused as a child. He may have had a rough childhood.'}
{'text': '(3) Illegal drugs are not inherently dangerous. \xa0They are dangerous in the way that any other risky activity is dangerous.'}
{'text': 'I think that the best solution to the problem of drug abuse is to remove the legal restrictions.'}
